org.objectweb.asm.jip
インタフェース FieldVisitor

既知の実装クラスの一覧:
EmptyVisitor
public interface FieldVisitor

A visitor to visit a Java field. The methods of this interface must be called in the following order: ( visitAnnotation | visitAttribute )* visitEnd.

作成者:
Eric Bruneton

メソッドの概要
 AnnotationVisitor visitAnnotation(java.lang.String desc, boolean visible)
          Visits an annotation of the field.
 void visitAttribute(Attribute attr)
          Visits a non standard attribute of the field.
 void visitEnd()
          Visits the end of the field.
 

メソッドの詳細

visitAnnotation

AnnotationVisitor visitAnnotation(java.lang.String desc,
                                  boolean visible)
Visits an annotation of the field.

パラメータ:
desc - the class descriptor of the annotation class.
visible - true if the annotation is visible at runtime.
戻り値:
a visitor to visit the annotation values, or null if this visitor is not interested in visiting this annotation.

visitAttribute

void visitAttribute(Attribute attr)
Visits a non standard attribute of the field.

パラメータ:
attr - an attribute.

visitEnd

void visitEnd()
Visits the end of the field. This method, which is the last one to be called, is used to inform the visitor that all the annotations and attributes of the field have been visited.
